Your father just died, right next to you, as you hang upside down from your seat belt. The sheet metal has sliced into his brain and blood pools into the car's headliner. A drunk driver was the cause of the wreck. After a year of rehabilitation you enter your first day of eighth grade. You're forced to sit next to and interact with the tribal cousins of your father's killer. - - Disenchanted with modern life one is granted a second chance. Two souls collide in the spiritual world and become one.